  "result": "1. Turn switch A on and leave it on for about 10 minutes.\n2. Turn switch A off.\n3. Turn switch B on.\n4. Immediately enter the room.\n5. The bulb that is lit is controlled by B.\n6. Touch the two unlit bulbs; the warm one is controlled by A, the cold one is controlled by C.\n\nWhy this works: Bulbs convert electricity to both light and heat, and heat lingers after the light goes out. By leaving A on long enough to warm its bulb, then switching to B just before entering, you encode three distinguishable states \u2014 lit (B), unlit-but-warm (A), and unlit-and-cold (C) \u2014 giving each switch a unique signature observable in a single visit.",
